<paragraph role="heading" id="set_up1" xml-lang="en-US" level="1">
Setting up Read Text Extension</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="set_up1.1" xml-lang="en-US" level="2">
Set up
</paragraph>
<list>
<listitem>
Click the icon on the menu bar or choose 
<emph>
Tools - Add-Ons - Read Selection...</emph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
Choose the program or website you want the extension to use and the command string or script.
</listitem>
<listitem>
<switchinline select="sys">
<caseinline select="MAC">
By default, the extension uses 
<emph>
/usr/bin/say</emph>
 as the external application and 
<emph>
-f '(TMP)'</emph>
  in the Command Line Options box. </caseinline>
<caseinline select="UNIX">
By default, the extension uses 
<emph>
/usr/bin/python</emph>
 as the external application and 
<emph>
"(ESPEAK_READ_TEXT_PY)" --language=(SELECTION_LANGUAGE_COUNTRY_CODE) --visible=false "(TMP)"</emph>
 in the Command Line Options box. 
</caseinline>
<caseinline select="WIN">
By default, the extension uses 
<emph>
wscript.exe</emph>
 as the external application and 
<emph>
"(TTS_WSCRIPT_VBS)" "(TMP)"</emph>
  in the Command Line Options box. You can use the command line to change the voice and rate of speech. The fastest rate of speech is 10 and the slowest is -10.
</caseinline>
<defaultinline>
By default, the extension uses 
<emph>
/usr/bin/espeak</emph>
 as the external application and 
<emph>
-f '(TMP)'</emph>
 in the Command Line Options box. 
</defaultinline>
</switchinline>
</listitem>
<listitem>
You can test the settings without saving them by 
<switchinline select="sys">
<caseinline select="MAC">
 holding down the Control key and clicking </caseinline>
<defaultinline>
 right-clicking 
</defaultinline>
</switchinline>
<emph>
OK</emph>
.
</listitem>
<listitem>
When you are satisfied with the settings, uncheck 
<emph>
Always show this dialogue</emph>
.
</listitem>
<listitem>
Click 
<emph>
OK</emph>
.
</listitem>
</list>
<paragraph role="heading" id="customize" xml-lang="en-US" level="2">
Customize
</paragraph>
<list>
<listitem>
You can use different external applications or websites to speak different languages or translate text.
</listitem>
<listitem>
If you want to view the dialog to change settings, use 
<emph>
Tools - Add-Ons - Read Selection...</emph>
</listitem>
</list>
